# Cancel an in-flight calibration step. The CalibrationManager drops
# the active capture buffers (intrinsic and/or handeye for the named
# camera, or for every camera if `camera` is left empty) and the
# physical_ai_server releases the on_calibration mutex so the student
# can resume recording / inference / training without waiting for a
# robot-type switch. Idempotent: safe to call when no step is active.
#
# camera: 'gripper' | 'scene' | '' (empty = cancel every camera)
string camera
---
bool success
string message
